This is an outstanding hotel. It has everything that I wanted in a hotel and they really delivered on that.  There are plenty of conveniences that make your stay enjoyable. The staff, from the people in the check in desk to the cleaning ladies, is very helpful, accommodating and friendly.   The laundry room has both washing machines and driers and you don't have to purchase detergent nor liquid softener as they have it readily available for free. I noticed that there is a staff member on site to ensure all stays tidy and properly functioning.   The gym equipment was just what I needed. They have a good set of dumbbells, some treadmills, and some other machines to get you a good enough workout.   Another great feature is the extended breakfast hours. Not sure if this is standard in larger cities, but breakfast was served from 7 to 12, which is extremely advantageous.   The hotel enjoys a favorable location; there is a shopping mall with plenty of restaurants, mostly in the basement floor, and it's within a 2 minute walk. Sanyuanqiao metro station happens to be right next to that same shopping mall, making it very practical to have dinner and take the metro right after.  The only issue I found was connecting to the internet; you need t enter phone number, wait for the text message with a code and then enter the passport number. I made several attempts to connect to no avail. When I brought it up at the fron desk, one of the girls came to my room and set it up in no time. Unfortunately, I stopped having access after 2 days.  Anyways, definitely staying in this hotel next time I'm in Beijing!!|2021-07-22 23:59:00"

We wanted a nice Christmas holiday, as we were unable to travel home to families for the holiday. We found the hotel on Trip.com. Although the room is small it is perfect for a couple. The staff were friendly on arrival and are able to speak some English but with a translation APP it is more than enough to communicate. We were also give cute Christmas boxes with an apple inside, which was a nice touch. The bed is super comfortable and the set up of the room is very space effective. The one concern we had was that the towels smelt like second hand smoke which was not great. There is a nice gym on the first floor, along with 3 washing machines and 3 dryers next to elevators on the right hand side. There is laundry detergent and fabric softener next to the machines and they are available for guests to use 24/7.  The location of the hotel is incredible. The line 10 subway station is a 3 minute walk away and downtown is 5 stops from the station on the same line. There is also a lovely Mall one stop away the Mall is The Grand Summit and has other tasty restaurants to enjoy. The Galleria Mall is a 3 minute walk from the hotel which has a nice supermarket and some decent restaurants. There is a Starbucks opposite the Hotel, it is a bit hidden as you need to cross the road and go down a few stairs. The fact that it‚Äôs hidden means there are not huge crowds of people.  I will definitely recommend this hotel to friends and family visiting Beijing.|2020-12-24 23:59:00"

As a patient with difficulty in choosing, I was really struggling to choose this hotel again and again, and the result was unexpectedly good! Great for young people! The hygienic environment is very good. I feel that the value for money is excellent, and the price performance ratio is very high. I recommend young people to live here. I ordered takeaway at night, and there was a robot delivering it to the door of the room. The front desk service was also very patient and enthusiastic, and finally I stored my luggage. The sound insulation of this hotel is really super good. Water and drinks are free. The location is good and it's close to the subway. However, we happened to catch up with the maintenance of the subway entrance, so we kept taking taxis to various attractions About 30 more! Only one small downside is that the room is a bit small!

The location is good. There is the Sanyuan Bridge subway entrance two to three hundred meters away, but the subway entrance is currently under construction and only connects to the airport special line. The environment is tidy, the facilities in the lobby and the room are relatively new, and there is a mobile phone holder at the head of the bed, hahahahaha~ The service is also very good, the service is enthusiastic, and the room calls are also answered quickly. The front desk has sufficient staff, and if you need help with check-in or other matters, it is handled efficiently. If you have to talk about the shortcomings: 1. The room space is definitely not very large, the bathroom is a bit small, and it is easy to touch the glass when raising your hand. It is probably a bit like the style of a compact hotel in the center of Japan. Fat people and big people may not be friendly, haha Hahahaha~ 2. The cleaning of the room could be more meticulous. The toothpaste on the inside of the sink was left by the previous guest. I stayed for three days and didn't get rid of it...I picked it off manually...the black table is also a little dusty obvious.

The transportation around the hotel is convenient, and there are bus stations and subway stations not far away; it not only has a grand appearance, but also has a simple and elegant interior decoration. There are not only board games for relaxation and entertainment in the lobby, but also a cafeteria for customers to use. The hotel staff are very enthusiastic, considerate and patient in service - the front desk work is meticulous and considerate, the cleaning staff will take the initiative to greet customers while doing their job well, and the duty manager has a professional and conscientious service attitude. The design of the guest room is still in a simple style, but there are all kinds of living utensils, and every part of the space is fully functional. What touched me was the various mirrors in the room. Among them, the magnifying mirror (not only for makeup, but also for checking whether the teeth are clean, very friendly to orthodontists) is my favorite, and I also like it The bedside lamp, the color of the light makes the room very warm. Looking forward to the next time I come to Beijing, I will stay at Huange Hotel again if I have the opportunity.

1. The hotel is a whole building, three minutes walk from the subway exit. 2. Booked a hotel for three nights! The hotel front desk called me the next day and asked if I would renew! Was still sleeping! Very annoyed! The most basic hotel services in hotel management. I would complain about the real feelings of staying in, there is no falsehood! I took my baby to Beijing for a trip to Beijing. I went to the family room of the hotel that I had booked before. I saw that the room was decorated before placing the order, so I specifically called the hotel to ask if there is an air purifier. I only placed the order after I was told. After arriving at the hotel on October 1st, first go to the front desk to check in and pay the room fee. Before paying the money, check with the front desk again if there is an air purifier. I was told again that there is an air purifier! Okay, pay the money and move in! When I walked into the elevator, I smelled a pungent smell of decoration. The rooms in the corridor are bigger and bigger than expected! So I immediately asked about the air purifier, the house sweeper actually took a bottle of air freshener to spray, saying that their hotel does not have an air purifier! After I checked with the front desk, I told me that there was indeed no air purifier! ! ! Well, I was deceived. On the first night, I was awake at three in the middle of the night, with a sore throat and headache, and stayed up all night. The child kept shouting that his throat had a sore headache the next day, and his husband said that he was unwell. Online checking is one of the symptoms of excessive formaldehyde! When I checked in on the 1st, the child had two unexplained nosebleeds during the day on the 3rd and the night on the 5th. The child had never had a nosebleed before. As a mother, I am very worried now. I am worried that staying in a room with severely excessive formaldehyde for four days will have a great impact on the health of the child. The people in the next room also said the room smelled! I don‚Äôt understand why people stay in the hotel if the formaldehyde exceeds the standard. The robot delivery and free supper in your hotel can‚Äôt make up for the fatal flaw of excessive formaldehyde! In addition, I discovered that the hotel had reduced the price before I checked in. It was a hundred lower than when I checked in! Too unreliable! I advise consumers, please keep your eyes open for your health, and be sure to refer to the evaluation before placing an order. Don't be attracted by some of his house's fancy decorations like me, and ended up living in a room with a serious excess of formaldehyde, which eventually harmed your children! Be sure to refer to the evaluation before placing an order!
